So, as I said, back in 1935 or 1936, I got us a 
portable soil testing kit.

06:22.047 --> 06:33.359
didn't take me long to see that these kits that were 
built up in the northern states just weren't worth

06:22.047 --> 06:33.359
a nickel in Texas.

06:33.379 --> 06:39.886
We had different conditions, so I took off and 
built my own. And the result of my work

06:42.709 --> 06:48.595
and the work being done under Fudge in the state 
chemist's lab. I can't think of the fellow's name.

06:55.709 --> 06:56.510
Asbury? No, no, old Asbury.

07:00.634 --> 07:02.797
No, let's let that ride.

07:06.441 --> 07:11.767
This, I'll cut that out too.

07:11.787 --> 07:12.608
But

07:29.547 --> 07:42.087
Oh, I built this kit, and I would go out to this farm 
and take soil samples and test them. And he

07:42.107 --> 07:44.390
wouldn't believe them. Certainly not. That's 
brand new stuff. He didn't do that. So I'd

07:48.537 --> 07:53.945
go and take this growing cotton. I'd go get a half a 
dozen leaves. off of this cotton that's just going

07:57.728 --> 08:01.173
to make about one bale and ten acres. I'd go down 
here, I'd get about a half a dozen leaves off of some

08:02.034 --> 08:09.204
cotton that's going to make about a half a bale and 
ten acres. I'd test them. Now his eyes would bug

08:14.912 --> 08:16.214
out.

08:19.318 --> 08:22.603
Now, I kept that up. There are a lot of interesting 
stories there that come up with as you go along

08:27.260 --> 08:28.582
through that. And in 1950,

08:29.864 --> 08:49.293
I guess it was,

08:29.864 --> 08:49.293
they talked the state chemist into running the 
analyses with the understanding that I wrote the

08:29.864 --> 08:49.293
recommendations.

08:52.037 --> 08:55.562
Now, in order to get the state chemist to do that, it 
took lots of doing. Because Fraps insisted there

08:57.162 --> 09:02.828
was no way in the world you could run a soil test and 
predict what happened. And he fought soil testing

09:04.429 --> 09:09.174
with everything that he had. Well, his successor 
Fudge was a little more liberal. And when I yanked

09:15.721 --> 09:27.152
him out of his marble chair and took him out in the 
country with me, I let him see what was going on. He

09:28.060 --> 09:37.809
then decided that he would go into it, and they went 
into it with the understanding that every soil

09:28.060 --> 09:37.809
sample was a dollar, which was all right. But that 
still wasn't satisfactory, so I, with another

09:40.071 --> 09:56.245
fellow, as I said, I can't think of his name, took a 
trip around the states that were using soil

09:40.071 --> 09:56.245
testing to get their ideas. among which was 
Oklahoma, Arkansas, Mississippi, Kentucky,

09:57.862 --> 10:05.351
Illinois, Iowa, and Missouri. We came back here 
and set up the laboratory we have here. I go to the

10:11.138 --> 10:16.885
laboratory here now and see what they're doing. 
It's amazing. Back in those days, we did

10:19.608 --> 10:22.772
everything by

10:26.262 --> 10:29.766
strong methods and awkwardness. Nowadays, 
you've got these electronic machines. They'll

10:36.834 --> 10:41.779
run the soil out now and give you analyses on that 
thing there that I never dreamed of. As I said,

10:42.580 --> 10:45.283
that's part of this thing that I mentioned way back 
here. The chemistry is just boiling. And what

10:49.267 --> 10:54.733
you're up to data in today, you're out of data on 
tomorrow. And that's the way it ought to be. That's

10:58.104 --> 10:58.725
fine. I hate to like Rip to be an old has-been, but 
then I'm not going to do the fighting and the

11:00.007 --> 11:10.321
working and the studying to stay up when I can get 
out here in the garden and have a good time.

11:13.306 --> 11:16.069
So that's another thing. And when I quit in 57, this 
soil testing laboratory was another one of my

11:16.089 --> 11:25.783
babies that was Well, it's certainly recognized 
throughout the state. A lot of people use its

11:30.088 --> 11:31.970
facilities. Yeah, we built several. We built two 
or three branch

11:33.813 --> 11:44.387
laboratories and regional laboratories. I 
always thought Oklahoma had the county, and

11:44.447 --> 11:50.134
Mississippi had the county, and I fought those. 
The county doesn't have anything more to do than

11:50.835 --> 11:53.779
run soil tests. he better fire him, and

