in my living around here is the ingenuity and the 
ability of the students. The radio tower on top of

13:01.521 --> 13:13.856
Milne Hall was put in, I would say, about 19, the 
summer of 1913 or maybe 14. And

13:13.876 --> 13:20.685
one morning we woke up. And a young fellow, his name 
was Cohen, rode a bicycle to and from work. And that

13:30.204 --> 13:33.507
darn bicycle was tied to the top of that radio 
tower. How in the name of common sense that bunch

13:35.670 --> 13:43.719
got that bicycle up there, I'll never know. They 
finally got it down, and I guess the fellow put it up

