16:02.141 --> 16:07.968
football and knew the way around. But, you know, we 
couldn't get with 11 men. So, well, no, we couldn't

16:11.472 --> 16:13.755
get 11. We had two that we organized as standing 
guards. With this bird, you know, at Thermopylae,

16:20.045 --> 16:24.209
you stand up there and need not let him pass. And 
their jobs were not to let anybody through. They

16:27.411 --> 16:31.135
did nothing about football, but they're both 
powerful men. And just don't let that other fellow

16:32.836 --> 16:35.378
through. You just take care of him. And be sure you 
get the man that's got the football.

16:43.785 --> 16:44.586
The others, played and the rest of us ran the team. 
Tommy Ogier was quarterback. Who was that? Tommy

16:52.390 --> 16:53.211
Ogier. You never heard of him? No, I haven't. He 
died here about three or four years ago. Well, we

16:59.340 --> 17:08.953
went out there and played the C Company and they 
thought a good chance to get even with the

16:59.340 --> 17:08.953
professors. The half of us didn't realize they 
were working fellows that had cut their teeth in

17:11.043 --> 17:23.538
big-time football, and for a little amateur 
company team to haul off and rough them up a little

17:11.043 --> 17:23.538
bit was just asking for trouble. So the morning 
after they played the C Company, there were about

17:24.759 --> 17:30.386
15 in the hospital. And the next time we played was 
the band.

17:38.376 --> 17:39.497
And the same thing happened. I know most of the band 
was in the hospital. And we weren't hurt. We were

17:45.216 --> 17:47.199
just taking the thing in the stride. Then Charlie 
Moran decided that I didn't, he says, I don't have a

17:49.342 --> 17:54.871
game for Saturday. How about you fellas playing 
Thursday or Friday? Playing the reserves, not the

18:00.880 --> 18:03.664
first team. Now a lot of boys think it's the first 
team. It wasn't the first team. Doggone it that

18:08.232 --> 18:21.512
morning before we were going to play, our center, 
Missouri Valley, had to have an appendix out. And

18:21.532 --> 18:33.029
they had a fellow they could put out on end that had a 
little sense about football but not a whole lot. So

18:34.391 --> 18:37.395
they elected me to take that center place.

18:39.991 --> 18:45.258
And I can assure you the fellow that was playing on 
the other side was using something beside his

18:39.991 --> 18:45.258
body. I think he had a club in his hand where it could 
be over. But man, oh man, the reserves beat us five

18:50.426 --> 19:05.567
to nothing just because that doggone replacement 
of mine let the halfback on the reserve team get

18:50.426 --> 19:05.567
outside him. And they finally brought him down on 
about the five yard line, and they did put the

19:10.518 --> 19:17.809
cross, they earned it, but we couldn't score.

19:21.194 --> 19:31.130
Next morning, President Miller issued one of the 
many foolish edicts that comes out of the

19:21.194 --> 19:31.130
president's office. He said, in the future, no 
member of the teaching staff will participate in

19:32.672 --> 19:37.740
any hazardous or dangerous games. That is the most 
foolish thing that ever happened. If you'd have

19:43.059 --> 19:47.587
handed a football at any of them, they'd have 
turned the ball like that. They wouldn't have even

19:48.248 --> 19:49.470
touched it. Man, how wicked we took. Five to 
nothing. It wasn't a bad game. But that was the

19:54.738 --> 19:56.481
cleanest game we played. The games against the 
company teams. The boys didn't use their head. But

20:03.853 --> 20:05.736
against the reserves, it was a clean game. But they 
were hitting and they were hitting hard.

